2C%20particularly%20if%20prices%20in%20the%20economy%20remain%20sticky%2C%20Deutsche%20Bank%20said.%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20are%20three%20major%20stumbling%20blocks%20for%20US%20stocks%2C%20according%20to%20Deutsche%20Bank.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bank%20pointed%20to%20three%20big%20economic%20risks%20to%20the%20market's%20blistering%20bull%20rally.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20stocks%20have%20seen%20stellar%20gains%20this%20year%2C%20but%20there%20are%20hurdles%20that%20could%20derail%20the%20bull%20rally%2C%20according%20to%20Deutsche%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20note%20to%20clients%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20bank%20highlighted%20three%20potential%20headwinds%20that%20could%20threaten%20the%20momentum%20in%20stocks.%20The%20benchmark%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20climbed%2026%25%20year-to-date%2C%20gaining%203%25%20in%20the%20last%20month%20alone%20on%20hopes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-trump-win-election-stock-market-outlook-strategy-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump's%20presidency%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20boost%20asset%20prices.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20whilst%20markets%20might%20look%20invulnerable%20right%20now%2C%20it's%20worth%20remembering%20there've%20actually%20been%20several%20wobbles%20this%20year%20already%2C%26quot%3B%20Henry%20Allen%2C%20a%20Deutsche%20macro%20strategist%2C%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSo%20given%20how%20markets%20have%20already%20reacted%20to%20various%20shocks%20this%20year%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20any%20one%20of%20these%20factors%20could%20drive%20a%20fresh%20selloff%2C%20particularly%20if%20they%20became%20a%20more%20persistent%20and%20longer-lasting%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20since%20valuations%20are%20more%20elevated%20now%20relative%20to%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20that%20means%20on%20paper%2C%20the%20scope%20for%20further%20gains%20is%20now%20more%20limited%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20three%20things%20the%20bank%20thinks%20could%20pose%20a%20risk%20to%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22739a18eb-5347-42ca-ad08-b93a08f1781d%5C%22%3E1.%20An%20economic%20downturn%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20economists%20think%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20on%20track%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoft-landing-economy-us-on-track-data-cooling-interest-rates-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoft-landing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20scenario%20in%20which%20inflation%20cools%20without%20sparking%20a%20severe%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20the%20economy%20weakens%20more%20than%20expected%2C%20that%20poses%20a%20major%20risk%20to%20equities%2C%20Allen%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20this%20summer's%20steep%20stock%20sell-off%20driven%20by%20weak%20jobs%20data%20and%20fears%20that%20the%20economy%20was%20stumbling%20after%20the%20Fed's%20aggressive%20rate-hike%20campaign.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFortunately%2C%20that%20month%20marked%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20of%20the%20US%20data%2C%20which%20then%20started%20to%20improve%20again.%20But%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20had%20a%20sizeable%20selloff%2C%20even%20though%20the%20data%20wasn't%20pointing%20to%20a%20recession%2C%20begs%20the%20question%20as%20to%20how%20severe%20it%20could%20have%20been%20if%20the%20data%20did%20start%20to%20point%20towards%20a%20recession%20and%20show%20an%20outright%20contraction.%20After%20all%2C%20we%20know%20that%20recessions%20are%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20things%20possible%20for%20risk%20assets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpectations%20for%20growth%20are%20also%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20higher%26quot%3B%20for%202025%2C%20Allen%20said%2C%20with%20Wall%20Street%20expecting%20GDP%20growth%20to%20remain%20above%202%25%20next%20year.%20That%20means%20it%20will%20be%20harder%20for%20the%20data%20to%20meet%20or%20exceed%20the%20market's%20expectations%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22168485d8-7cf0-4aed-ad1d-82356a8a97ce%5C%22%3E2.%20Geopolitical%20turmoil%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGeopolitical%20tensions%20escalated%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20causing%20oil%20prices%20to%20spike%20and%20stock%20prices%20to%20see%20a%20swift%20decline.%20Stocks%20also%20stumbled%20last%20week%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatacms-storm-shadow-missiles-rain-down-on-russia-first-time-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20US-%20and%20British-made%20missiles%20at%20Russia%2C%20leading%20Russia%20to%20retaliate%20by%20launching%20a%20new%20hypersonic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-oreshnik-what-know-about-experimental-missile-used-against-ukraine-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emissile%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20markets%20are%20clearly%20very%20jittery%20to%20any%20geopolitical%20escalation%2C%20it's%20just%20that%20in%20each%20case%2C%20the%20worst-case%20fears%20of%20a%20wider%20conflict%20didn't%20actually%20materialize.%20However%2C%20if%20a%20fresh%20conflict%20or%20a%20major%20escalation%20did%20happen%2C%20then%20we%20know%20from%20recent%20experience%20that%20markets%20can%20react%20very%20negatively%2C%20as%20seen%20after%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022%2C%26quot%3B%20Allen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299ea31f2-b889-43a6-9e1a-7ea5261b4862%5C%22%3E3.%20Rising%20inflation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-october-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20cooled%20from%20a%20high%20of%20around%209%25%20in%202022%2C%20with%20consumer%20prices%20rising%202.6%25%20year-over-year%20in%20October.%20That%20was%20on%20par%20with%20economists'%20expectation