20wanted%20to%20live%20permanently.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rio%20de%20Janeiro%20skyline%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6748512e9f2901eb603788a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoel%20Balsam%20traveled%20to%2017%20countries%20last%20year%20alone%20but%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20Brazil's%20culture.%3Cp%3EPakawat%20Thongcharoen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJoel%20Balsam%20grew%20up%20in%20Ottawa%20and%20dreamed%20of%20traveling%20the%20world%20from%20a%20young%20age.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20a%20travel%20writer%2C%20the%2034-year-old%20has%20spent%20most%20of%20the%20last%20decade%20overseas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBalsam%20realized%20during%20the%20pandemic%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20based%20in%20Canada%20and%20found%20a%20home%20in%20Brazil.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20this%20time%20last%20year%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20on%20a%20two-week%20trek%20in%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20burned%20out.%20I%20wanted%20to%20scream%20into%20the%20snowy%20mountains%2C%20%26quot%3BWill%20I%20ever%20find%20a%20place%20where%20I%20belong%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Canada%2C%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BThe%20City%20That%20Fun%20Forgot.%26quot%3B%20I've%20always%20wanted%20to%20see%20what%20was%20out%20there%20beyond%20my%20quiet%20backyard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20political%20science%20and%20journalism%20at%20university%20in%20Montreal%2C%20I%20spent%20four%20months%20backpacking%20in%20South%20America.%20The%20last%20country%20I%20visited%20on%20the%20trip%2C%20Brazil%2C%20blew%20my%20mind.%20Locals%20in%20Rio%20de%20Janeiro%2C%20where%20I%20celebrated%20Carnaval%20in%202013%2C%20said%20I%20was%20just%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarioca%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20what%20locals%20call%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20amazed%20by%20their%20passion%20for%20their%20music%2C%20dancing%2C%20and%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sense%20of%20pride%20they%20call%20%26quot%3BBrasilidade.%26quot%3B%20I'd%20never%20experienced%20anything%20like%20that%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b3fed6d-752b-449a-a969-4f34ae701391%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20for%20somewhere%20else%20like%20Rio%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVowing%20to%20return%2C%20I%20went%20back%20to%20Canada%20and%20worked%20at%20a%20weekly%20newspaper%2C%20but%20the%20call%20to%20travel%20came%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20year%20teaching%20English%20in%20Madrid%20and%20traveled%20across%20Europe%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Southeast%20Asia.%20To%20make%20extra%20money%20and%20continue%20my%20writing%20career%2C%20I%20wrote%20trending%20news%20articles%20for%20a%20Montreal-based%20website%20that%20allowed%20me%20to%20work%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20basing%20myself%20in%20Medellin%2C%20Colombia%2C%20and%20Oaxaca%2C%20Mexico%2C%20for%20a%20few%20months%20each%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20Rio%20in%202018%2C%20hoping%20to%20feel%20that%20spark%20again.%20However%2C%20the%20energy%20wasn't%20as%20I'd%20remembered.%20There%20had%20just%20been%20a%20divisive%20election%20that%20saw%20former%20President%20Ja%C3%ADr%20Bolsonaro%20come%20to%20power.%20I%20continued%20traveling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20on%20a%20four-month%20road%20trip%20across%20the%20southern%20United%20States%20with%20my%20then-girlfriend%2C%20a%20photographer.%20We%20teamed%20up%20to%20do%20stories%20for%20top%20international%20publications%20like%20Time%2C%20the%20Guardian%2C%20and%20National%20Geographic.%20We%20traveled%20to%20Morrocco%20and%20Armenia%20so%20I%20could%20write%20guidebooks%20for%20Lonely%20Planet.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20living%20my%20dream%20life.%20Then%20the%20pandemic%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnsure%20of%20when%20international%20travel%20might%20return%2C%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20buy%20an%20apartment%20in%20Montreal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20love%20Montreal%2C%20I%20struggled%20mentally%20during%20the%20pandemic%20curfews%20and%20the%20long%20Canadian%20winters.%20In%202022%2C%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20broke%20up%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20the%20urge%20to%20find%20somewhere%20to%20call%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273131a0a-6779-4892-a1bb-cc1a1ac5cfe5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELit%20up%20again%20in%20Brazil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20I%20traveled%20to%2017%20countries%20for%20work%20and%20to%20search%20for%20a%20place%20to%20live.%20Everywhere%20I%20went%2C%20I%20asked%20people%20why%20they%20chose%20to%20live%20in%20the%20place%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202023%2C%20I%20felt%20burned%20out%20from%20my%20search%2C%20which%20culminated%20in%20that%20mountain%20meltdown%20in%20Nepal.%20To%20see%20if%20I%20could%20find%20belonging%20with%20other%20wandering%20souls%2C%20I%20took%20a%20cruise%20with%20digital%20nomads%20from%20Spain%20to%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20there's%20anything%20wrong%20with%20traveling%20full-time%2C%20but%20I%20found%20myself%20butting%20heads%20other%20passengers%20who%20seemed%20to%20want%20to%20live%20exactly%20as%20they%20did%20back%20home%2C%20just%20more%20cheaply%20and%20in%20better%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20cruise%20landed%20in%20Salvador%2CBrazil%2C%20most%20cruisers%20carried%20on%20traveling%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20palm%20trees%2C%20the%20way%20locals%20told%20stories%2C%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20country's%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20lit%20me%20up%20about%20Brazil%20as%20it%20had%20during%20my%20first%20visit.%20I%20felt%20the%20energy%20had%20relaxed%20since%20president%20Lula%20was%20re-elected%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20traveled%20to%20the%20island%20Parintins%20for%20a%20Brazilian%20festival%2C%20Boi-Bumb%C3%A1.%20As%20thousands%20sang%20and%20danced%20in%20performances%20that%20told%20indig