er%20for%20%26quot%3BChallengers%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20write%20the%20script%20for%20%26quot%3BQueer%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20the%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJustin%20can%20be%20more%20precise%20about%20this%2C%20but%20I%20remember%20that%20we%20said%2C%20'What%20is%20unfinished%2C%20we%20want%20to%20try%20to%20finish%2C'%26quot%3B%20Guadagnino%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20in%20doing%20that%2C%20we%20have%20to%20understand%20why%20it%20was%20unfinished%20and%20how%20Burroughs%20would%20have%20finished%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuadagnino%20said%20the%20pair%20also%20spoke%20to%20Oliver%20Harris%2C%20a%20leading%20expert%20on%20Burroughs'%20life%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20American%20literature%20at%20Keele%20University%2C%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20film's%20production%20notes%2C%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20queer.%20I'm%20disembodied%26quot%3B%20came%20from%20Burroughs'%20journals%2C%20and%20reflects%20his%20unease%20about%20identifying%20as%20gay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a2fa469-745f-43d5-9b8c-7df57173eb98%5C%22%3EThe%20final%20section%20of%20the%20movie%20is%20based%20on%20the%20novel's%20epilogue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20%26quot%3BQueer%26quot%3B%20showing%20actors%20in%201950s%20Mexico%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6747508f9f2901eb60375d8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20film%20is%20mainly%20set%20in%20Mexico%20City.%3Cp%3EA24%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20part%20of%20the%20film%20is%20set%20two%20years%20after%20the%20trip%20to%20the%20jungle%2C%20and%20shows%20Lee's%20return%20to%20Mexico%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20based%20on%20the%20novel's%20epilogue%2C%20where%20Lee%20searches%20for%20Allerton%2C%20discovers%20he%20has%20left%20Mexico%20City%2C%20and%20dreams%20about%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20a%20dream%2C%20the%20movie%20enters%20another%20hallucinogenic%2C%20surreal%20sequence%2C%20where%20Lee%20sees%20himself%20in%20a%20doll%20house.%20In%20the%20following%20scene%2C%20Lee%20and%20Allerton%20are%20in%20a%20room%2C%20and%20Allerton%20places%20a%20glass%20on%20his%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20shoots%20at%20the%20glass%20with%20a%20gun%2C%20but%20hits%20Allerton's%20forehead%20instead.%20There%20is%20no%20blood%2C%20and%20Allerton%20soon%20disappears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20scene%20may%20be%20based%20on%20Burroughs%20accidentally%20shooting%20and%20killing%20his%20wife%20Joan%20Vollmer%20while%20they%20lived%20in%20Mexico%20City%2C%20which%20he%20wrote%20about%20in%20the%201985%20introduction%20to%20%26quot%3BQueer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20forced%20to%20the%20appalling%20conclusion%20that%20I%20would%20never%20have%20become%20a%20writer%20but%20for%20Joan's%20death%2C%20and%20to%20a%20realization%20of%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20this%20event%20has%20motivated%20and%20formulated%20my%20writing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Burroughs'%20biography%2C%20he%20used%20a%20glass%20on%20her%20head%20as%20a%20target%2C%20in%20a%20similar%20fashion%20to%20the%20scene%20in%20%26quot%3BQueer%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20prove%20he%20was%20good%20at%20shooting%2C%20but%20hit%20her%20forehead.%20Burroughs%20was%20convicted%20of%20murder%20and%20given%20a%20two-year%20suspended%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20film's%20final%20scene%20shows%20Lee%20back%20at%20his%20apartment%2C%20old%20and%20dying.%20Lee%20imagines%20Allerton%20appearing%20in%20his%20bed%2C%20draping%20a%20leg%20over%20his.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuadagnino%20told%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Few.com%2Fqueer-ending-explained-daniel-craig-luca-gudagnino-decipher-dream-sequence-8751437%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Entertainment%20Weekly%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20this%20scene%20is%20meant%20to%20show%20Lee's%20lasting%20and%20%26quot%3Bprofound%26quot%3B%20connection%20with%20Alle