div%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20more%20eyes%20we%20have%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20it%20is%20that%20someone%20will%20do%20something%20about%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20recently%20passed%20Wildlife%20Week%2C%20they%20carried%20out%20a%20campaign%20where%20they%20made%20frames%20of%20various%20wild%20animals%20and%20plants%20and%20presented%20them%20to%20school%20classrooms%2C%20panchayat%20houses%2C%20and%20government%20offices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20go%20to%20schools%20and%20ask%20the%20children%20%E2%80%98what%20is%20wildlife%E2%80%99%2C%20they%E2%80%99ll%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20zebras%2C%20tigers%2C%20or%20lions%2C%20even%20if%20the%20kids%20have%20never%20seen%20them.%20But%20if%20you%20ask%20someone%20to%20identify%20a%20bustard%2C%20not%20many%20will%20get%20it%20right.%20The%20local%20wildlife%2C%20because%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20eyes%20on%20it%2C%20is%20silently%20depleting.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20make%20the%20children%20a%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%20because%20they%20will%20have%20to%20take%20this%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jagdish%20Pooniya%2C%2032%2C%20an%20audit%20inspector%20from%20the%20Dhava%20Doli%20Wildlife%20area%2C%20and%20one%20of%20Sharvan%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20key%20collaborators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHands-on%20approach%20to%20wildlife%20conservation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20vital%20aspect%20of%20Sharvan%E2%80%99s%20work%20has%20been%20his%20relationship%20with%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20local%20government%20officials.%20As%20someone%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20the%20department%20for%20over%20five%20years%2C%20he%20has%20seen%20firsthand%20the%20challenges%20they%20face.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20only%20one%20small%20room%20with%20one%20staff%20member%2C%20and%20they%20don%