a%20collaboration%20with%20multi-Grammy%20winner%20Jacob%20Collier%20and%20Anoushka%20Shankar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Rinchen%20Norbu%20Wangchuk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F382543%2Fvarijashree-venugopal-grammy-award-nomination-a-rock-somehwere-jacob-collier-anoushka-shankar-bengaluru%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Tribal%20Community%20In%20Maharashtra%20Is%20Using%20Zero-Budget%20Videos%20to%20Fight%20for%20Their%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20quiet%20village%20of%20Dhadgaon%20in%20Nandurbar%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20a%20transformative%20movement%20is%20taking%20root.%20%E2%80%98Aadiwasi%20Janjagruti%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20grassroots%20initiative%20led%20by%2050%20passionate%20community%20members%20%E2%80%94%20is%20revolutionising%20how%20tribal%20communities%20connect%20with%20governance%20and%20the%20world.%20Through%20captivating%20videos%2C%20films%2C%20and%20documentaries%2C%20they%20are%20creating%20a%20hyperlocal%20communication%20network%20that%20empowers%20tribes%20to%20address%20everyday%20challenges%20and%20engage%20with%20the%20Government%20like%20never%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20it%20all%20began%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20Aadiwasi%20Janjagruti%20traces%20back%20to%202016%2C%20when%20Nitesh%20Bhardwaj%20(33)%2C%20one%20of%20its%20founders%2C%20arrived%20in%20Dhadgaon%20for%20a%20fellowship%20programme.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Nitesh%20was%20passionate%20about%20filmmaking%20but%20had%20no%20plans%20for%20long-term%20involvement%20in%20the%20village.%20His%20connection%20with%20the%20community%20began%20unexpectedly%20%E2%80%94%20through%20a%20group%20of%20eager%20high%20school%20students%20curious%20about%20video%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20equipment%20or%20resources%2C%20Nitesh%20started%20teaching%20the%20students%20how%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5